			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<em>We are a company obsessed with providing excellent support</em>. Our small and scrappy&nbsp;team has been working hard on educating and helping our customers, and now it&#39;s&nbsp;time to add a new <strong>Customer Champion</strong> to the tasty mix.</p>
<p>
<strong>Customer Champion</strong> is a tough job. They are the conduit between Wistia (that&#39;s us!)&nbsp;and our awesome customers. Our small team (myself, Max, and Jordan) spends most&nbsp;of the day talking to current and prospective customers, whether it&#39;s through&nbsp;support emails, phone calls, or Twitter conversations.</p>
<p>
Support at Wistia <em>isn&#39;t</em> separated out into a call center, or micromanaged.&nbsp;It&#39;s all about doing right by our customers. We also develop our product by&nbsp;listening to customer feedback: what they find valuable, what workflows they&nbsp;are having trouble with. This means support always has a voice at the table.</p>
<p>
Here are a some other things that are key to an excellent <strong>Customer Champion</strong>:</p>
<p>
<strong>Leveling Up, Constantly.</strong></p>
<p>
We love getting the type of feedback that makes us better at what we do. We&nbsp;also work on skillsets that will help us provide better support - like learning&nbsp;to write excellent front- and back-end code. We&#39;re endlessly curious, and take&nbsp;interest in every aspect of the business. We know a friendly answer is great,&nbsp;but an educated &amp; friendly answer is even better!</p>
<p>
<strong>Growth by Automation.</strong></p>
<p>
As a small team, we&#39;ve learned what parts of our message can be amplified using&nbsp;automation. By shooting video that educates new customers on using the the&nbsp;product, we made their onboarding experience easier and more consistent. We&#39;ve&nbsp;also learned some things cannot be scaled - the way we talk to customers is&nbsp;through our own voice, and not a script.</p>
<p>
<strong>Relentless, Dogged Determination.</strong></p>
<p>
We answer a lot of email. On the whole, our awesome customers make it easy. But&nbsp;even on hard days, we won&#39;t throw the towel in because we know how&nbsp;important our mission is. We grind because of how crucial support is to our&nbsp;business.</p>
<p>
<strong>You MUST:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Be ready to interact with customers, whether that is by email, phone,&nbsp;message-in-a-bottle, whatever.</li>
<li>
Be highly self-directed. We don&#39;t hold hands or provide daily direction here. Our goal is to help you find the most important things to work on, and trust you from there.</li>
<li>
Be hopelessly addicted to solving problems.</li>
<li>
Be naturally high-energy and capable of long days full of fun and hard work.</li>
</ul>
<p>
This isn&#39;t your typical heavy hours, low pay job. We expect the best, so we pay&nbsp;for the best. We also provide health and dental benefits, because it just feels&nbsp;right to take care of our team.</p>
<p>
<strong>Other benefits include (but are certainly not limited to):</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A rad office space with more natural light than you thought was possible. There are also dark, cavernous areas if you fear monitor glare.</li>
<li>
A world-class expert in bizarre alcohol infusions.</li>
<li>
A ping pong table and ample competition.</li>
<li>
Making lots of videos that usually involve crazy antics.</li>
<li>
A team of people who really care about the product and company they&#39;re building.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
Our office is in Davis Square in Somerville, MA. We&#39;re right on the Red Line, surrounded by great restaurants, bars, parks, and a 2 minute walk from the best coffee shop in Boston. Does this all sound right for you? Then we&#39;d love to hear from you!</p>
]]></description>
