			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Good day!</p>
<p>
Since the early days, Wistia has had a focus on hiring the right people. We&rsquo;ve worked hard on our hiring process and are really proud of the team we&rsquo;ve assembled. Now, we&rsquo;re looking for someone to take this process to the next level.</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for a detail-oriented people person to build, run, and scale our hiring process as we grow from 20, to 40, to 1,000 people. This won&rsquo;t be as simple as writing job postings, nay. You&rsquo;ll be wrangling applicants, championing for our culture, and figuring out how to get the best people to beat a path to our door.</p>
<p>
<strong>This role is critical to the growth of our company. It&rsquo;s about finding the most talented people we possibly can, tracking them, and reeling them in. After all, we&rsquo;re only as good as our team.</strong></p>
<p>
While experience in recruiting, HR, and people operations is great, it is not a requirement to excelling in this position.</p>
<p>
You&rsquo;ll be:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Mapping out our hiring strategy and managing this process across the entire organization.</li>
<li>
Forging the systems and analysis to maintain a ridiculously high quality bar.</li>
<li>
Managing our communication and onboarding practices to get people up-to-speed quickly and efficiently</li>
<li>
Working with everyone across the company to bring dreams into reality</li>
</ul>
<p>
Things that matter to us:</p>
<ul>
<li>
You are looking for work you&rsquo;ll love. We work a lot because we like it, and we like each other. It&#39;s weird.</li>
<li>
You are humble. We want superstars who don&#39;t need to tell us they are.</li>
<li>
You are thoughtful and creative.</li>
<li>
You are analytical. We are data-driven and that&#39;s important to us.</li>
<li>
You are a man and/or woman of action. Planning is great, doing is better.</li>
<li>
You love hats, as in wearing multiple. Headware is purely optional.</li>
<li>
You like hypo-allergenic labradoodles.</li>
<li>
You enjoy picking up coffee and booze for friends. Just because.</li>
</ul>
<p>
This is a well-paid, full time job with all the standard corporate benefits like health and dental.</p>
<p>
<br />
Other benefits include (and may or may not be limited to):</p>
<ul>
<li>
A <a href="http://home.wistia.com/medias/ertztr03r9">rad office space</a> with more natural light than you can shake a stick at.</li>
<li>
A world-class expert in <a href="http://wistia.com/blog/wistiavideofest-bens-infusatorium/">bizarre alcohol infusions</a>.</li>
<li>
A <a href="http://home.wistia.com/medias/4d86047c7f">ping pong table</a> and ample competition.</li>
<li>
Making lots of videos that usually involve<a href="http://wistia.com/blog/product-launches/"> crazy antics</a>.</li>
<li>
A <a href="http://wistia.com/blog/2012-wrap-up/">team of people</a> who care deeply about what they&#39;re doing</li>
</ul>
<p>
Our office is in Davis Square in Somerville, MA. We&#39;re right on the Red Line, surrounded by great restaurants, bars, parks, and a 2 minute walk from the best coffee shop in Boston.&nbsp; We are moving to Cambridge in October -- ask us about it!</p>
<p>
<br />
If this sounds like it might be fun, get in touch.&nbsp; This is a limited time offer :)</p>
